STUDENT GRADE CALCULATOR – TEST CASES
===================================

TEST CASE 1: Valid Input – Grade A
---------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Priya
Marks: 95

Expected Output:
Marks: 95/100
Grade: A
Message: Excellent work! Outstanding performance!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 2: Valid Input – Grade B
---------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Rahul
Marks: 85

Expected Output:
Marks: 85/100
Grade: B
Message: Very Good! Keep it up!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 3: Valid Input – Grade C
---------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Anu
Marks: 72

Expected Output:
Marks: 72/100
Grade: C
Message: Good effort! You can do even better!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 4: Valid Input – Grade D
---------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Karthik
Marks: 65

Expected Output:
Marks: 65/100
Grade: D
Message: Fair performance. Work harder next time!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 5: Valid Input – Grade F
---------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Meena
Marks: 45

Expected Output:
Marks: 45/100
Grade: F
Message: Don't give up! Learn from mistakes and try again!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 6: Boundary Value – Minimum Marks
------------------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Arjun
Marks: 0

Expected Output:
Marks: 0/100
Grade: F
Message: Don't give up! Learn from mistakes and try again!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 7: Boundary Value – Maximum Marks
------------------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Sneha
Marks: 100

Expected Output:
Marks: 100/100
Grade: A
Message: Excellent work! Outstanding performance!

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 8: Invalid Input – Negative Marks
------------------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Ramesh
Marks: -10

Expected Output:
Error message displayed:
"Invalid input! Marks must be between 0 and 100."
User is asked to re-enter marks.

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 9: Invalid Input – Marks Above 100
-------------------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Kavya
Marks: 150

Expected Output:
Error message displayed:
"Invalid input! Marks must be between 0 and 100."
User is asked to re-enter marks.

---------------------------------

TEST CASE 10: Invalid Input – Non-numeric Value
----------------------------------------------
Input:
Student Name: Deepak
Marks: abc

Expected Output:
Error message displayed:
"Please enter a valid integer value."
User is asked to re-enter marks.

===================================
END OF TEST CASES
